commitmsg: Try to deal with changed circle-ci environment.

Add and use domain blocklist.

This hooks up the machinery to create and use a blocklist based on
data/domain_blocklist.txt. Currently we only filter `localhost`.

Use bulk inserts and upserts in session upload task.

Using upsert's via "insert on conflict do nothing" should remove all
client side conflict errors. Bulk inserts avoid the ORM overhead and
use only a single insert statement per uploaded session batch.
Fix rst style in deploy docs [ci skip].
Add a link to project description on the homepage.
Add comments, avoid counting duplicate dropped URLs.
Filter out URLs containing private IP addresses.
Provide pre-compiled wheels for binary Python dependencies.
Reformat requirements files, so hashes are actually used.

Pin Python requirements to specific hashes.

In some cases two hashes are given for a project, one for a source
distribution and one for a universal wheel. Platform specific binary
wheels do not yet exist for Alpine Linux.
Split Python requirements into build, binary and pure-python files.
Add quantitative metrics about the incoming data.
Don't emit statsd counters for zero-increments.

Move delete/upload tasks onto their own celery queues.

This allows delete tasks to be processed quickly, and avoids them being
blocked by a backlog of upload tasks.
Remove stackframe content and exception values from Sentry.
Retry database insertion on conflict errors.
Store and delete session data into and from database.
Extend db model tests to test delete cascading.
Fix DB test isolation problem by fixing the scope of the db fixture.
Add url, user and session database tables.
Require start_time for sessions, filter out URLs containing HTTP auth.
Use the same code layout for delete and upload tasks.
Make upload logic testable on its own.
Add min/max range validation to fields.
Update to new combined session data format.
Document expected upload payload format and validate it.
Move JSON decoding from web app to backend celery tier.
Document alembic and make it more easily accessible.
Use new mailing list as contact point.
Use different IP detection on circle.
Try waiting on Postgres in circle builds.

Stop building on travis.

Maintaining a non-docker environment is too much hassle.
Add Postgres database to the stack.

Replace docker-machine instructions with direct docker.

We require Docker for Mac on Mac OS now.
Fix code to take away package name prefix.
Pass Bucket as a string to head_bucket (#1)
Enable docker builds on circle ci.
Document deployment requirements, test connections during app startup.
Add Amazon S3 wrapper class and dummy test implementation.
Hook up dummy data tasks to store incoming data in Redis.
Handle GZIP encoded POST bodies to upload API.
Add CORS support and some basic request checks.
Pin redis container to latest available version in AWS.
Automatically use all available CPU cores.
Add sentry/statsd and automatic counters/timers per task and request.
Next attempt with Redis in a container.
Another try to get the container to talk to Redis on the host.
Make Redis cache available on celery/web workers and add heartbeat view.
First prototype of a skeleton app that does nothing.
Filter out all `.local` domains, adjust end date.
Extend domain blocklist to block certain top-level domains.
Add tab_id to upload schema and extend sessions table.
Change tld method contract to return None if no tld could be extracted.
Capture and retry SQLAlchemy internal TypeError during upload.

Integrate client side blocklist.

The list is reduced to those domains which still respond to DNS lookups.

Adjust miracle_block script to take public suffixes into account.

Instead of doing a full hostname match, it now does a preliminary
endswith check and follows up with a check against the bloom filter.
Apply domain blocklist based on domain's public suffix.
Allow comments in domain_blocklist and centralize its parsing.
Update end date based on launch data.
Add analysis script to get recurring URL stats, refs #2.
Always pull docker hub for latest images while building.

Enable SSL hostname checks in the database production environment.

The SSL cert used in CI testing and local development does not provide
a hostname match.

Extend Redis ping by testing a write operation.

During failover between a Redis primary and read-replica the application
can temporarily be connected to a Redis instance in read-only mode.
Remove unused AWS S3 bucket code.
Check user header against allowed character list.
Avoid constructing an SQL statement via string concatenation.
Turn upload task into a class.

Optimize delete orphaned urls query.

On a dummy data set with one million sessions, this now consistently
uses an index-only scan on the ``sessions.url_id`` index.
Validate JWE structure in HTTP upload API.

Remove orphaned URLs after user deletion.

When deleting a user, delete cascading inside the database only removes
all associated sessions. We now manually collect all URLs associated
with any of the user sessions and queue a second job. This job checks
all the URLs and removes those which are no longer associated with any
session, i.e. they were unique to the deleted user.
Add a end date for the experiment, closes #4.
Add ``data.user.delete_hours`` metric to track user participation time.
Add creation date to users table.
Emit HSTS headers and add CSP for the homepage.

Create a HTML-based front page.

Also some minor style changes.
Correct CORS headers for jwk and stats HTTP APIs.

Remove support for GZIP encoded upload requests.

Since the upload request is now encrypted, applying compression to it
afterwards doesn't reduce the size. Similarily stop GZIP compressing
Celery tasks.
Change the upload API to expect a JWE encrypted body.
Change crypto helper module to use JWE RSA-OAEP/A256GCM encryption.

Use base64 encoding for keys.

This avoids having to deal with the significant newlines in the PEM data.
Add crypto helper module for RSA-OAEP based encryption.
Update Python dependencies and add new cryptography dependency.

Stop connecting to the S3 bucket on worker startup.

The bucket isn't yet used.

No longer set up a DB connection from the web app.

We can add this back later, once this is actually used.
Capture exceptions in the startup process and send them to Sentry.
Add missing s3transfer dependency of newer boto3.
Add help messages and progress logging to command line scripts.

Database migration, renaming "full" column and optimizing indices.

"full" is another reserved word. Also adding indices on session foreign
keys, so delete cascading on deleting a single user or url has a chance
to finish in reasonable time.
Avoid sqlalchemy ORM in non-test code.
Set up logging for alembic migrations.

Database migration, pluralizing all table names.

This avoids conflicts between the Postgres built-in "user" table and
ours and removes the need to quote "user" in all SQL statements.
More rst changes, used preview now [ci skip].
Try quoting backslashes in rst [ci skip].
Make it easier and document production database access.
Add a miracle_block script to remove blocklisted URLs from the database.

Don't actually tag the "latest" image, as it already has the correct name.

Also the docker version in circle-ci is old and recommends `tag -f`,
which is gone in newer versions.

Try to fix circle-ci again.

Apparently it really doesn't like naming conflicts.
Avoid docker image name conflicts in circle-ci.
Use full docker image name to match circle-ci.

Update dependencies.

Only provide hashes for wheel files of pure Python dependencies.
Implement and test the frontend_s3 Kinesis job.
Add stream metrics and test process_records.
Add tests for KCL process checkpointing and updating max_seq.
Define a custom KCLProcess class and let the tests use it.
Add tests for KCL processor init/shutdown.
Turn individual record processors into functions, add batching.
Add KCL BaseRecordProcessor to handle common stream processing logic.
Add skeleton MCL/MultiLangDaemon config and job.
Restrict outside network access off docker containers.
Decrease Kinesalite delay to speed up tests.

Make bucket/kinesis clear logic more robust.

Also correctly pass in pre-created kinesis client into celery app.

Refactor common delete_stream code into its own function.

Also let _delete_frontend_stream use it, so it properly waits.
Update deploy docs with AWS service permissions.
Add year/month to bucket path, use more compact JSON.
Add back local DynamoDB, for Kinesis MultiLangDaemon.

Add JRE and amazon_kclpy.

Also add other missing Python dependencies.

Next stepping stone, put payload into Kinesis instead of Redis.

This still uses Celery to keep track of how far into each stream/queue
data was written / read.
Add a direct Kinesis Python client and test support.

Remove local DynamoDB, add local Kinesis (kinesalite).

Also move back web server port to 8000.
Tweak bucket code, try to explicitly close open sockets.
Allow almost arbitary data schema in uploads.

Target cryptography < 1.7, to be openssl 1.0 compatible.

The Python 3.6 docker image is still based on Debian Jessie.
Add local DynamoDB, change default web port to 80880.
Remove Postgres and alembic db migration support.
Upload data to S3 instead of Posstgres.

Use minio to provide a AWS S3 compatible service for local testing.

Also change bucket logic to use the minio instance in tests.

Bring back AWS S3 code.

This reverts commit 5b467dff81dcd51d0ede89d0eee9f710bd2c2551.
Update to v2 API, which moves the user id into the payload, closes #5.
Remove delete and stats API endpoints.

Switch Docker image to be Debian based and install numpy.

Numpy is currently not compatible with the previously used Alpine Linux.
Add a LRU cache to DNS validation.
Revert celery workers back to multiprocessing.
Switch celery worker to use gevent for concurrency.
Drop sessions with a start_time in the future or more than 2 weeks old.
Use c-ares based DNS resolver in gevent by default.
Add script to calculate daily sessions per user.
Summarize weekly_recurrence results as max/mean/medium/min results.

Test our bloom filter against the top 100 domains.

It shouldn't filter out any of them, except three known adult domains.

Update blocklist.

This removes some domains which are purely ads/tracking domains,
and not used exclusively for adult content.
added source dia file for db_schema & svg with background

Don't rely on DOCKERHUB_REPO env variable in normal test runs.

Cirlce-ci doesn't expose any environment variables to pull requests,
as they might contain credentials, like our DOCKER_PASS variable
used in the deployment section.
Add SVG version of database schema, curtesy of lars.

Weekly recurrence script requires at least one week participation time.

So far the script counted all users, even those that where created
recently, skewing the results.

Update blocklist, decrease false positive rate.

The blocklist file is still only 12kb.

Increase maximum valid session duration to 21 days.

Also substitute out-of-range values with a under/overflow value of the
correct type to dinstinguish them from missing values.
